package( USEPKG Units PyAnaMisc USEEXT Numpy )

######################################################################

Package providing simple common module to set up numpy and matplotlib.

A simple:

  from PyAna import *

at the top of a plotting script will provide numpy, matplotlib and
matplotlib.pyplot (including aliased to np, mpl, plt respectively) and
math, os and sys modules. Other customisations are currently:

  * matplotlib.pyplot.legend(..): numpoints=1 by default (recover standard with numpoints=2
  * matplotlib.pyplot.legend(..): draggable by default (disable with nondraggable=True)
  * Interactive plotters can be closed with shortcut key 'Q'.

